Review control description: (3) A UCB shall invest in the shares of a co-operative society only if the bye-
laws of the recipient society provide for the retirement of share capital
contributed by it;

Review control description: A scheduled UCB, fulfilling the following conditions, shall be eligible to
undertake repo transactions in corporate bonds:
(1) Applicable minimum CRAR plus 1 per cent;

Review control description: The Board shall review the following aspects of non-SLR investment at least at
quarterly intervals:
(1) Total business (investment and divestment) during the reporting period;

Review control description: As per paragraph 120 and 121 above, a UCB fulfilling the following criteria shall
have the option to accept deposits from other UCBs:
(1) Applicable minimum CRAR plus 1 per cent;

Review control description: The criteria for empanelment of brokers shall, at the minimum, include the
following:
(1) SEBI registration;

Review control description: (2) Transactions entered into directly with counterparties, i.e., where no
brokers are involved, shall be excluded to arrive at the total transactions
through brokers;

Review control description: (3) If for any reason it becomes necessary to exceed the aggregate limit for
any broker, a UCB shall record the specific reasons for such breach and
the Board shall be informed, post- facto;

Review control description: (4) In case of repo transactions both the legs of the transaction, i.e.,
purchase as well as sale shall be included to arrive at the volume of total
transactions;

Review control description: The concurrent audit shall, at the minimum:
(1) Ensure that in respect of purchase and sale of securities, the concerned
department has acted within its delegated powers;

Review control description: Further, the repeal of these directions,
instructions, or guidelines shall not in any way prejudicially affect:
(1) any right, obligation or liability acquired, accrued, or incurred thereunder;
